Description: Foot and lower wall fragment of pottery amphora(?); fine pale buff clay with some mica; flaring foot with broad resting surface; inside, remains of a burnt black resin (?); lowest part of wall and oujtside of foot glazed; upper part of wall and underside of foot reserved; inscriptions under foot.
Curator's comments: The shape is that of a table amphora, not transport jar.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.024)
Stacey et al 2010 / Coatings and contents: investigations of residues on four fragmentary sixth-century BC vessels from Naukratis (Egypt) (p.20, fig.1b, p.21, table.1)
